article.headline: IUPUI 74, Indiana Southeast 59
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- David Barlow had 17 points and five assists to lead IUPUI to a 74-59 victory over Indiana Southeast Wednesday night. Barlow shot 6-of-12 from the floor and had seven steals for the Jaguars (2-2). Fred Kounkorgo added 13 points on 6-of-8 shooting and grabbed eight rebounds as IUPUI outrebounded Indiana Southeast 40-33. Drew Conner came off the bench to score nine points on 4-of-4 shooting for the Jaguars. IUPUI had a 41-26 lead at halftime that grew to 26 points with 9:16 left in the game. Rick Bodiford led the Grenadiers (3-2) with 14 points and five rebounds. Indiana Southeast's bench outscored the IUPUI reserves 31-19 but the Grenadiers had 28 turnovers which IUPUI turned into 22 points.
